questions.explanation:
The primary purpose of namespaces is to prevent **name collisions**. As projects grow and use multiple libraries, it becomes likely that two different authors define functions or variables with the same name. Namespaces solve this by grouping identifiers into distinct scopes, accessed via the `::` operator.

```cpp
namespace Graphics { void init() { /* GPU setup */ } }
namespace Audio   { void init() { /* sound setup */ } }
// No conflict — call Graphics::init() or Audio::init()
```

